The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Standard Chartereds net profit increased 25 per cent to Rs 1,706 crore from Rs 1,364 crore in 2007-08 fiscal. The banks balancesheet grew 25 per cent to Rs 73,445 crore from Rs 58,891 crore a year ago. Growth has come across key businesses, including financial markets, transaction banking, corporate finance advisory, SME banking and wealth management amongst others, Stanchart CEO (India and south Asia) Neeraj Swaroop said.                            
	 Greenply Industries has reported net sales of Rs 151 crore for the quarter ended March 31, 2008, a jump of 36 per cent from Rs 111 crore posted in the corresponding period of the last fiscal. Net profit for the fourth quarter stood at Rs 8.7 crore, a growth of 29 per cent from Rs 6.7 crore posted in the year ago period.                             
	 123 Greetings will provide access to 20,000 free e-cards for over 3,000 special occasions and events. The site has launched a new application for Orkut users who will be able to see what cards other people have sent in their network and review the highest ranked ones.                             
	 Rohit Ferro-Tech has posted a profit after tax of Rs 80.2 crore on a sales of Rs 613.1 crore. On a year-on-year basis, the companys sales have increased 208 per cent from Rs 199.1 crore and net profit 317 per cent from Rs 19.2 crore.                             
	 PayMate India has closed its second round of investment of $9 million, led by Mayfield Fund and participation from existing investors  Kleiner Perkins Caufield amp; Buyers and Sherpalo Ventures  for an undisclosed stake in mobile payment company PayMate.                            
	 Empee Sugars and Chemicals Ltd is setting up an integrated sugar complex with a capacity of 5,000 tonnes crushing per day in Ambasamudram Taluk of Tirunelveli district in Tamil Nadu. The Rs 515-crore complex will be located across 300 acres and it is expected to go on stream by 2009 end.                             
	 Nuance Communications has launched T9 Nav, a mobile discovery solution that provides a faster way to access all features, applications and content on a mobile device.                             
	 Tata Motors is organising a free monsoon check up campaign for passenger cars and utility vehicles in the city from June 15 to July 15.                            
	 Virgin Mobile has announced its vSleek offer. On purchase of every vSleek priced at Rs 4,799, Virgin Mobile users can avail a lifetime validity voucher, a starter user kit and 2,000 minutes of free local calls to any network.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
